author: Ted Crow, The Plain Dealer
title: Watching the leaves turn in this week's cartoon-caption contest
text:
Last week's winners. Ted Crow, The Plain Dealer Readers: Email your caption for this cartoon by Plain Dealer artist Ted Crow to pdq@plaind.com . Include your hometown. Write "Humor Us" in the subject line. Mail: Cartoon-caption contest, Plain Dealer Publishing Co., Skylight Office Tower, 1660 West 2 nd St., Suite 200, Cleveland, Ohio, 44113. Deadline is noon Wednesday. Note: No phone entries. Last week's winners:
The fourth estate has 'scaled' back on newspaper deliveries.
- N. E. Nilsson, Columbiana
Hon, did you forget to pay the paperboy again?
- Otto Wegert, Gates Mills
Both were disappointed: one expected The Plain Dealer and the other, to spawn.
- George Eversman, Rocky River
Frank now understood why most people received their news from the internet.
- Doug Bahniuk, University Heights
I think I live a little too close to the lake.
- Bob Weiser, Twinsburg
Le Journal's enhanced Food section.
- Maryalice Walerski, Northfield
